  <scopecontent id="aspace_e794c21f65d0f3ef23d11c7654d1ec15">
    <head>COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
<p>Blueprints, drawings, photographs, pamphlets, and printed material of this firm and its successor, Furst &amp; Tilton (after 1950) of Chicago, Illinois. Many items relate to the Seabury-Western Theological Seminary at Evanston, Illinois; others pertain to churches, mainly in Milwaukee, Wisconsin, and cities in Illinois; also schools, public buildings, business establishments and residences.</p>  </scopecontent>
  <separatedmaterial id="aspace_7dba6d99d1863f573843e17db5e010cc">
    <head>SEPARATED MATERIAL</head>
<p>Paper: Brief History of St. John's Church - Ithaca, N.Y., <unitdate>1822-1955</unitdate>, A.G. Whitcomb. <extref href="http://rmc.library.cornell.edu/ead/htmldocs/RMM02308.html">See Acc. #2308.</extref> </p><p> Catalogue: "Ecclesiastical Appointments of Distinction." Morhouse-Gorham Co., Chicago, Ill. For Pamphlet Collection.</p>  </separatedmaterial>
